= Kimodo Motion Generator =

#type: node
#context: sop
#tags: kimodo, motion, ai, kinefx, animation

Generates 3D human motion from a text prompt using NVIDIA Kimodo, outputting a
77-joint SOMA skeleton (animated + rest poses) plus a skinned body mesh, all
compatible with Houdini KineFX.

== Overview ==

The node connects to a running [Kimodo|https://github.com/nv-tlabs/kimodo]
inference server (resident mode: the model is preloaded once). Press __Generate__
to submit a prompt; the finished NPZ is downloaded over HTTP into __Download Dir__
and the skeleton is rebuilt each frame. The server can run on this machine or a
remote GPU box — set __API Server URL__ accordingly.

== Quick Start ==

# Start the Docker services (`docker compose -f docker-compose.bridge.yaml up text-encoder -d`, then `up api -d`).
# Set __Prompt__ and __Duration__, then press __Generate__. Watch __Status__; the
  node cooks automatically when the NPZ has downloaded.
# Set the Houdini frame range to match the clip and play back.
# To get a deforming body: drop a __Labs/KineFX Joint Deform__ (`kinefx::jointdeform`)
  and wire input 0 = __Rest Geometry__ (output 2), input 1 = __Capture Pose__
  (output 1), input 2 = __Animated Pose__ (output 0).

== Parameters ==

API Server URL:
    URL of the running `kimodo_server`. Default: `http://localhost:8001`.
    Point this at the GPU host if the server runs elsewhere.

Download Dir:
    Local folder where finished NPZ files are downloaded from the server over
    HTTP. Default: `$HIP/kimodo_cache`.

Prompt:
    Natural language description of the desired motion.
    Examples: "a person walks forward", "someone waves their hand".

Duration (s):
    Length of the generated motion in seconds. At 30 fps, 3 s = 90 frames.

Model:
    Kimodo model variant. Default: Kimodo-SOMA-RP-v1.1.

Force Regenerate:
    Bypass the server cache and re-run inference even if a matching clip exists.

Constraints File / Constraints JSON:
    Optional [Kimodo constraints|https://research.nvidia.com/labs/sil/projects/kimodo/docs/key_concepts/constraints.html]
    that steer the generated motion to hit spatial targets — a root 2D path or
    waypoints, full-body keyframes, or end-effector (hand/foot) targets. Provide a
    list of constraint dicts: either point __Constraints File__ at a `*.json`
    (e.g. one exported from the Kimodo demo), or paste it into __Constraints JSON__
    (which takes precedence). Targets are in Kimodo's space: Y-up, metres, +Z
    forward, with the root at XZ = (0, 0) on frame 0 — the same world space this
    node outputs. Simplest type, a `root2d` waypoint set:
    {{{
    [{"type": "root2d", "frame_indices": [0, 90], "smooth_root_2d": [[0,0],[2,1]]}]
    }}}
    Leave both empty for unconstrained generation.

:input 0 — Root Path / Waypoints (optional):
    Connect geometry to build a `root2d` constraint without writing JSON. Each
    point's world XZ becomes a `smooth_root_2d` target (Houdini XZ maps 1:1 to
    Kimodo's space). Points carrying an integer `frame` point attribute become
    sparse waypoints at those frames (you control the timing); otherwise the points
    (in order — e.g. a resampled polyline) are spread evenly across the clip as a
    denser path. The result is appended to any JSON constraints above.

Generate:
    Submits the prompt to `<API Server URL>/generate` and returns immediately with
    a job ID. A background thread polls for progress, so Houdini stays responsive.
    When done, the NPZ is downloaded to __Download Dir__, __NPZ Path__ is set to it,
    and the node recooks.

Cancel:
    Cancels the job. The resident server can't interrupt an already-running
    generation — Cancel stops a queued job or discards the result.

Status:
    Read-only. Shows the live job state: Queued, Running... (Ns), Downloading...,
    Done (Ns), Failed, or Cancelled.

NPZ Path:
    The `.npz` the node reads to build the skeleton (a file field, *.npz). Set by
    Generate, or point it at any compatible NPZ by hand to load a clip produced
    outside this node — no Generate or server needed.

== Output Geometry ==

Four outputs, all in the same world space. World rotations use Houdini's
row-vector convention (transposed from Kimodo's matrices).

:output 0 — Animated Pose:
    Per-frame animated skeleton. Carries `name`, `path`, `parent_id`, `transform`
    (float[9] world rotation) and `localtransform` (float[16] local 4x4).

:output 1 — Capture Pose:
    The A-pose rest skeleton the mesh is bound to (feet on floor). `name` +
    `transform`. Use as the rest skeleton for the deformer.

:output 2 — Rest Geometry:
    The SOMA77 body mesh in its bind pose, with a KineFX `boneCapture` attribute
    (weights + bind from Kimodo's skinning). Drive it with `kinefx::jointdeform`.

:output 3 — T-Pose:
    A T-pose skeleton (`name` + `transform`) for reference / retargeting.

Deform graph: `kinefx::jointdeform` with input 0 = output 2, input 1 = output 1,
input 2 = output 0 — the body follows the animation and returns to bind at rest.

== SOMA77 Skeleton Hierarchy ==

{{{
Hips (0)
  Spine1-Spine2-Chest
    Neck1-Neck2-Head-HeadEnd/Jaw/LeftEye/RightEye
    LeftShoulder-LeftArm-LeftForeArm-LeftHand  [+ fingers 15-38]
    RightShoulder-RightArm-RightForeArm-RightHand  [+ fingers 43-66]
  LeftLeg-LeftShin-LeftFoot-LeftToeBase-LeftToeEnd  [67-71]
  RightLeg-RightShin-RightFoot-RightToeBase-RightToeEnd  [72-76]
}}}

== Notes ==

* The server preloads the model and loads weights from the local HuggingFace
  cache offline; the weights must be cached first (a prior generation, or
  `huggingface-cli download nvidia/Kimodo-SOMA-RP-v1.1`).
* The model stays resident in VRAM while the server runs — stop the api container
  to free it.
* __mock mode__ (MOCK_MODE=1) returns `dev_reference.npz` without inference, for
  HDA development without a GPU.
* Port 8000 is reserved by Docker Desktop on Windows; the API defaults to __8001__.
* Results are cached by prompt + duration + model; enable __Force Regenerate__ to
  bypass the cache.

